## 1. URL request and response

A URL is Uniform Resource Locator. It acts as a web address to different webpages. Every URL on the internet work on a request-response basis. The browser requests the server for a webpage and the response by the server would be the content of the webpage. This web content is then displayed on the browser.

URL Request - Requesting a web server for content to be viewed by the user. This HTTP request is triggered whenever you click on a link or open a webpage.

URL Response - A response for the request irrespective of success or failure. For every request to the web server, a mandatory response is provided by the web server and most of the times this would be the respective content requested by the user.

## 2. Run a simple HTTP request and explain response headers, status codes

Instead of the browser requesting for the content of the webpage, Python can be used for the same. A HTTP request to the web server can be sent with the requests library and the response can be examined. Typically every request receives a response with response headers and status code details.

Let us request for the web content for the Monash University front webpage with the URL - https://www.monash.edu/. The requests library can be used to work with webpages and web content. A request is made to get the content of the webpage with the get() method.


```python
import requests

monash_web_url = "https://www.monash.edu/"
response = requests.get(monash_web_url)
```

A response is received from the web server. This response will have response headers and status codes associated to that particular request.
Response headers give the detailed information about the request made to the web server.


```python
response.headers
```




    {'Content-Type': 'text/html; charset=utf-8', 'Transfer-Encoding': 'chunked', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Vary': 'Accept-Encoding, Accept-Encoding', 'Cache-Control': 'max-age=0, private', 'Pragma': 'cache', 'Server': 'openresty', 'X-Content-Type-Options': 'nosniff', 'X-Cache': 'HIT from squizedge.net', 'Date': 'Thu, 20 Feb 2020 02:00:15 GMT', 'Age': '61', 'Via': '1.1 squizedge.net', 'X-upgrade-enabled': 'off', 'X-Frame-Options': 'SAMEORIGIN', 'Expires': 'Thu, 20 Feb 2020 02:30:14 GMT', 'X-Request-ID': '13690024-41c9-4a17-95fb-ff6331c6d576', 'Content-Encoding': 'gzip'}



Every response will have a status code. The status codes indicate whether a specific HTTP request has been successfully completed.
Responses are grouped in five classes:

- Informational responses (100–199)
- Successful responses (200–299)
- Redirects (300–399)
- Client errors (400–499)
- Server errors (500–599)

Let us check the response status code for the HTTP request we placed


```python
response.status_code
```




    200



The response has a status code of 200. This is a successful response and hence there should be relevant content of the webpage in the obtained response. This can be checked by printing the content. This content received is the HTML source code of the webpage


```python
response.content
```

Understanding the underlying causes are the first steps to eradicating terror.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div>ANARCHISM AND EXTREMISM,</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div>CHANGE IT.</div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="3.32" data-freeze="4.72">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWe&rsquo;ve waged war on ending wars. Our <em>Gender, Peace and Security Centre</em> seeks out roadblocks to peace and demolishes them. We&rsquo;ve partnered with the Department of Foreign Affairs to help shape policies that work in Asia and beyond.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE WAR, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="5.24" data-freeze="5.36">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWhen human rights are being trampled, we&rsquo;re on the front line. Across issues including LGBTIQ rights, racism, prisons and more, our <em>Castan Centre for Human Rights Law</em> is asking the right questions: What&rsquo;s getting better? What isn&rsquo;t? What needs to change? \t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE CENSORSHIP, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="5.96" data-freeze="6.48">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWhen countries pit themselves against each other, all our lives are on the line. Our international law researchers are determined to put an end to the madness by identifying better ways to negotiate in high-stakes situations.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE&nbsp;IT, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="6.6" data-freeze="6.96">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tOur international relations researchers are working to create a generation of critical thinkers who proactively and positively challenge the status quo. \t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE&nbsp;IT, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="7.4" data-freeze="7.56">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tThe <em>Monash Institute of Cognitive and Clinical Neurosciences</em> is home to brain imaging research that&rsquo;s identifying why some humans can&rsquo;t help but agree &ndash; even when the stakes are high.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE&nbsp;IT, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="8.08" data-freeze="8.08">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tThe war on drugs has failed. Current laws affect groups that are already marginalised. We&rsquo;re proud to be part of <em>Students for Sensible Drug Policy</em>, dedicated to developing drug policy reform that works, based on principles of public health and human rights.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE DRUG&nbsp;LAW, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="8.97" data-freeze="9.52">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tSociety is hesitant to discuss high-cost, addictive behaviours such as gambling, problem drinking and misuse of drugs. Our <em>Institute of Cognitive and Clinical Neurosciences</em> is identifying the fundamental brain processes behind addiction, and translating those findings into accessible treatment.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE ADDICTION, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="9.92" data-freeze="10.04">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tHumans are partly to blame for freak weather that destroys our economies and environment. We owe it to the Earth to fix this. In the meantime, our <em>Centre for Excellence of Climate Extremes</em> is improving weather predictions and developing strategies to reduce devastation.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE FREAK&nbsp;WEATHER, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="10.65" data-freeze="10.65">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tMore than 2 billion people have inadequate access to clean water. Our <em>Sustainable Development Institute</em> is spearheading a transformative global project, working directly with the poorest communities to build safer, healthier systems.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE DIRTY&nbsp;WATER, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="11.32" data-freeze="11.56">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tGenocide is still a reality. The scale of human suffering is mind-numbing. Condemning isn&rsquo;t enough. Our <em>Castan Centre for Human Rights Law</em> as well as the Centre for Gender, Peace and Security are on the frontlines, safeguarding asylum seeker and refugee rights.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE HUMANITARIAN&nbsp;CRISES, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="11.84" data-freeze="12.12">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tThe cost of an environmental disaster is high. A single event can affect ecosystems, living standards and community health. Our <em>Disaster Resilience Initiative</em> is changing the way communities respond to natural disasters, limiting their severity and helping to prevent them from happening at all.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE ENVIRONMENTAL DISASTER, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="12.72" data-freeze="12.88">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tIt&rsquo;s actually not too late to save the planet. We&rsquo;re at the forefront of efforts to stop climate change and environmental devastation. Among <em>UN</em> delegations, international networks of leading scientists and even the <em>Scientific Committee on Antarctic Research</em>, our researchers are world-leading.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE GLOBAL&nbsp;WARMING, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="14.36" data-freeze="15.28">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tEach week in Australia, at least one woman is killed by a man. In a domestic setting, one in four children sees male violence. It has to stop. Our <em>Gender and Family Violence</em> researchers are reforming prevention by training law enforcement and changing legal responses to better protect the vulnerable.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE DOMESTIC&nbsp;VIOLENCE, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="15.44" data-freeze="16.12">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tSome situations are tinderboxes, instantly escalating from tense to violent. What ignites civil unrest? Our <em>Radicalisation Project</em> examines the establishing factors, then assists in forming policies to better pre-empt and prevent situations that lead to violence.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE STREET&nbsp;RIOTS, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="16.88" data-freeze="16.88">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tMore than one billion children live in areas affected by combat. Our <em>Educational and Developmental Psychology</em> degree prepares counsellors to rise to the challenges presented by a volatile world and guide their students to a better future.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE BOMBING&nbsp;KIDS, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="18.56" data-freeze="18.72">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tSoldier&rsquo;s heart, shell shock, combat disease. PTSD affects veterans and civilians everywhere. Our <em>Healthy Sleep Clinic</em> plays a critical role in improved treatment for insomnia and other traumatic stress-induced symptoms, providing a first step towards relief.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE PTSD, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="19.4" data-freeze="19.92">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWhy do we play global games of chicken? Our School of <em>Psychological Sciences,</em> applies principles of psychology to topical issues, digging to the root of controversy and current events to work out the why behind retaliation and other destructive behaviours.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE MUTUALLY ASSURED DESTRUCTION, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="20.92" data-freeze="22.4">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tOur Biological Sciences researchers have collaborated with other scientists to create a process that could end ivory trade forever. By changing how countries debate the topic, their solution pairs emotional intelligence with science to help resolve the debate and save these species.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE POACHING, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="23.16" data-freeze="23.76">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tAcross education, law, social science and politics we&rsquo;ve investigated the motivations behind the phenomena of populism in our documentary series <em>A Different Lens</em>. \t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE IT, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="24.96" data-freeze="26.2">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tThe internet moves at lightning speed, and the law can&rsquo;t keep up. As cyberbullying and trolling become increasingly common, our Education faculty is focused on examining their impact and developing strategies to protect the vulnerable from being drowned out.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE HATE SPEECH, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="26.84" data-freeze="27.24">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWe need a revolution. So we&rsquo;re starting one. We kicked it off with our Net Zero initiative: by the year 2030, we&rsquo;ll be the first Australian university powered by 100 percent renewable energy, acting as a living lab to prove that a sustainable future is possible.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE OUR FUTURE GOING UP IN SMOKE, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="28.12" data-freeze="28.52">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tConflict. Persecution. Eviction. We&rsquo;re seeing unprecedented numbers of displaced people denied access to the most basic right: safety. Our <em>Border Crossing Observatory</em> presents new insights on the topic, while in sharp relief, our <em>Australian Border Deaths Database</em> aims to prevent grave tragedies from becoming banal statistics.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE SOCIAL&nbsp;INJUSTICE, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="28.88" data-freeze="29.2">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tBeing safe in our own homes should be a right, not a privilege. Our Civil Engineering department serves as a leader in engineering for extremes, protecting society by making our infrastructure more resilient to the pressures of fire, flooding and attacks. \t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE UNSAFE HOUSING, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="30.16" data-freeze="30.64">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tEach year, more than 700,000 people die from diseases carried by blood-feeding insects. Eighty percent of the world&rsquo;s population is at risk. Our <em>Institute of Vector-Borne Disease</em> works to develop new treatments, saving hundreds of thousands of lives.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE DISEASE SPREADING, CHANGE&nbsp;IT.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="31.36" data-freeze="31.92">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWhen it comes to eating disorders, anorexia is by far the biggest killer. We developed the <em>Butterfly Eating Disorder Day Program</em>, using evidence-based treatment with individuals as young as 12 to help them beat this debilitating condition. \t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE EATING DISORDERS, CHANGE&nbsp;THEM.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="32.04" data-freeze="32.08">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tBy 2020, 75 percent of Australia&rsquo;s population will be overweight or obese, with serious health consequences. Our Centre for <em>Obesity Research and Education</em> is fighting back, identifying preventative strategies and safe management of the disease.\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-cta">\r\n\t\t\t<div>IF YOU DON&rsquo;T LIKE OUR EATING HABITS, CHANGE&nbsp;THEM.</div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t\t<div></div>\r\n\t\t</div>\r\n\t</div>\r\n</div><div class="content-layer content-item content-future" data-start="32.6" data-freeze="33.04">\r\n\t<div class="video-left-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-video-container"></div>\r\n\t<div class="video-right-pad"></div>\r\n\t<div class="changeit-content-container">\r\n\t\t<div class="changeit-description">\r\n\t\t\tWe owe it to respect our elders. ## 1. GET and POST calls to retrieve response objects - using urllib2, requests, JSON etc


There are mainly two types of requests which can be made to the web server. A GET request/call or a POST request/call.

GET call - GET is used to request data from a specified source. They are one of the most common HTTP requests. They are usually used to only receive content from the web server. An example would be to receive the content of the complete webpage.

POST call - POST is used to send data to either update details or request specific content from the web server. In a POST call, data is sent and then a response can be expected from the web server. An example would be to request content from a web server based on a particular selection from a drop-down menu. The selection option is upadted while also respective content is sent back.

Let us scrape a list of the fotune 500 compaies for the year 2018. The website from which the data is to be scraped is https://www.zyxware.com/articles/5914/list-of-fortune-500-companies-and-their-websites-2018.

![image.png](attachment:image.png)

It can be seen on this website that the list contains the rank, company name and the website of the company. The whole content of this website can be received as a response when requested with the request library in Python


```python
import requests
import pandas as pd
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

web_url = 'https://www.zyxware.com/articles/5914/list-of-fortune-500-companies-and-their-websites-2018'
response = requests.get(web_url)

print('Status code\n', response.status_code)
print('\n--\n')
print('Content of the website\n', response.content)
```

## 2. Using bs4 (and lxml) to parse the structure and access different elements within a HTML or XML

bs4 is a Python library which parses through HTML content and understands the complete structure of the content. The response content can be passed to a BeautifulSoup method to obtain a soup object which looks very structured.


```python
soup_object = BeautifulSoup(response.content)
print(soup_object)
```

    <div class="insight-body">
                                    
                Did you know that year 2013 is the first year after 1987 which had all its digits as distinct. ## 3. Manipulate it into a tabular structure - explore the schema

To be able to accurately extract relevant data from the webpage, it is important to explore the schema and understand the structure of the webpage. A good way to do this is to inspect the webpage directly on a web browser.
<br>

To do this,
- Open the webpage on a browser
- Right click on the data content to be extracted
- Click on 'Inspect' or 'Inspect element' option

This will open a console window which shows the real time HTML code corresponding to the web content. Now identify the type of HTML tag which contains all the data along with any id names or class names associated to that HTML tag. In our case, the data is enclosed in the 'table' HTML tag with the class name 'data-table'. This information can be used to search for the web content directly in our soup object with the find_all() method. This will return a soup object.


```python
data_table = soup_object.find_all('table', 'data-table')[0]
data_table
```

The first element of the list contains the column names 'Rank, Company and Website'. The next elements of the list contain soup objects which contain the company data including the rank. This data can be extracted in a loop since the structure for all the list elements is the same.

- An empty dataframe fortune_500_df is created with the column names 'rank', 'company_name' and 'company_website'
- The index is initiated to zero
- A for loop is designed to go through all the elements of the list in order and extract the rank, company name and company website from the list element which are enclosed in the 'td' HTML tag. A find_all() will return a list of td tags.
- The '.text' attribute can be used to just pick the text part from the tag. In our case this is the rank, company name and the compnay website
- These values are then put into the dataframe and the index value is incremented


```python
fortune_500_df = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['rank', 'company_name', 'company_website'])
ix = 0

for row in all_values[1:]:
    values = row.find_all('td')
    rank = values[0].text
    company = values[1].text
    website = values[2].text
    
    fortune_500_df.loc[ix] = [rank, company, website]
    ix += 1
    
fortune_500_df.head()
```
